- The integer array parameter `nums` must not be null.
- The length of the integer array `answer` is equal to the length of the integer array `nums`.
- Each element in the integer array `answer` is the absolute difference between the corresponding elements in the arrays `leftSum` and `rightSum`.
- The integer array `leftSum` is the sum of elements to the left of the index `i` in the array `nums`. If there is no such element, `leftSum[i] = 0`.
- The integer array `rightSum` is the sum of elements to the right of the index `i` in the array `nums`. If there is no such element, `rightSum[i] = 0`.